        <button
          type="button"
          id="close-modal-btn"
          class="text-stone hover:text-primary transition-all text-lg cursor-pointer"
        >
          ✕
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">1. The Pomodoro Method</h4>
        <p>
          The Pomodoro Technique is a time management method developed by Francesco Cirillo. It uses a timer to break work down into intervals, traditionally 25 minutes in length, separated by short breaks (typically 5 minutes).
        </p>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">2. Structured Cycle</h4>
        <p>
          The standard routine is:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-4 flex flex-col gap-1">
          <li><strong>Focus Session:</strong> Work for 25 minutes.</li>
          <li><strong>Short Break:</strong> Rest for 5 minutes.</li>
          <li>Repeat the cycle 4 times.</li>
          <li><strong>Long Break:</strong> Take a longer 15-minute break.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="font-semibold text-primary">3. Customizing Your Timer</h4>
        <p>
          Expand the Timer Settings to adjust focus lengths, short breaks, long breaks, and cycles to fit your specific schedule.
        </p>
      </div>
      <button
        type="button"
        id="modal-ok-btn"
        class="button-primary text-xs py-2 px-5 mt-2 self-end cursor-pointer"
      >
        Got it
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

